		<g:HTMLPanel>

			<div class="content">

				<div class='{style.left}'>
					<div class='{style.section}'>
						<div class='{style.sideBar}'>
							<p class='{style.sideheaderFont}'>Welcome to Cloud Pier’s Lighthouse</p>
							<p class='{style.sideFont12}'>Lighthouse is a proof-of-concept demo of Cloud Pier’s 
                                                            application / PaaS matchmaking. Using the service, one can search,
                                                            browse and discover cloud platforms, taking into account the developer’s
                                                            application requirements and PaaS characteristics. <br></br>
                                                            Stay tuned for additional Lighthouse capabilities, all based on Cloud Pier open source technology.<br></br> 
                                                            For more on Cloud Pier, please visit www.opencloudpier.org.
								<a href="http://www.opencloudpier.org">www.opencloudpier.org</a>
							<br></br>
                                                        Cloud Pier was created via the EU co-funded research project, Cloud4SOA. 
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class='{style.sideImages}'>
							<img src="cloud4soadashboard/gwt/c4s/imgs/eu.gif" alt="EU logo"
								title="EU logo" class='{style.euImg}' />
							<img src="cloud4soadashboard/gwt/c4s/imgs/fp7_small.gif" alt="FP7"
								title="FP7" class='{style.fp7Img}' />

						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class='{style.center}'>
					<div class='{style.section}'>
						<div>
							<img src="cloud4soadashboard/gwt/c4s/imgs/lighthouse.jpg" alt="MatchmakingLightHouse"
								title="Clouds" class='{style.matchmakingImg}' />
						</div>
						<div class='{style.banner}'>

							<p class='{style.titleFont}'>Find the best PaaS for your application!</p>

						</div>
						<div style="clear:both;"></div>
						<div>
							<div class='{style.column3}'>
								<div class='{style.columnHeader}'>
									<p class='{style.columnHeaderFont}'>Create your app's profile</p>
								</div>
								<div class='{style.columnText}'>
									<p class='{style.textFont}'>
                                                Specify what you need from a Cloud provider, by creating a profile of your application.
                                                A profile specifies, for example, that you need a Java provider and a DB with enough storage.                                                                            
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class='{style.column3}'>
								<div class='{style.columnHeader}'>
									<p class='{style.columnHeaderFont}'>Matchmaking</p>
								</div>
								<div class='{style.columnText}'>
									<p class='{style.textFont}'>
                                                When you search, your app's profile is compared to all providers’ profiles in the system.
                                                We rank the results based on how well they fit your app's profile.    
                                                                        </p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class='{style.column3}'>
								<div class='{style.columnHeader}'>
									<p class='{style.columnHeaderFont}'>Browsing</p>
								</div>
								<div class='{style.columnText}'>
									<p class='{style.textFont}'>
                                                You can also browse providers’ characteristics using our facet browser, and select,
                                                                            for example, only the ones that use MongoDB.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
                                                <div class='{style.centerDisclaimer}'>
                                                    <p class='{style.textFont}'>
                                                    Coming Soon
                                                    </p>        
                                                    <p class='{style.textSmallFont}'>
                                                            You may notice some upcoming features hinted at within this proof-of-concept, such as some
                                                            extra columns in search results showing user and system ratings, as well as user-defined SLA
                                                            monitoring templates once a platform is selected. These are part of the full Cloud Pier
                                                            open- source solution, available at www.opencloudpier.org, and coming soon
                                                            to future deployed Lighthouse services. In the meantime, please tell us your thoughts
                                                            at contact@opencloudpier.org!
                                                        </p>
                                                        <p class='{style.textSmallFont}'>
                                                            Disclaimer: The PaaS offerings included in the matchmaking results are based on sample data gathered
                                                            from the Cloud4SOA research project.
                                                            While profiles are updated based on new tests, they might not reflect up-to-date data at
                                                            the time of use, and do not reflect direct data from the provider.  SLA info is user-defined,
                                                            and does not represent contract offered by the providers listed.
                                                        </p>
                                                </div>                                                
					</div>
				</div>
